cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with training and analysis strategies for convolutional neural networks (CNNs) using image segmentation and entropy-based diversity criteria. This is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research, as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of large, high-resolution images, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) research.
